        <body>
            <div id="header">
                <div class="column1">
                    <img src="res/img/GS_logo.gif" alt="GreatSchools.net logo" width="200" height="81"/>
                </div>

                <div class="column2">
                    <h3>
5 Steps to Choosing a Great School for Your Child</h3>
                    <p>
Welcome, ${sessionScope.context.user.firstName} ${sessionScope.context.user.lastName},
                        <br/>
    Use these links to get started or continue your school selection process.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="column3">
                                               ${sessionScope.context.user.email}
                    <br/>
Not you?
                    <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/cgi-bin/logout/${sessionScope.context.stateOrDefault.abbreviation}/">Sign out</a>
                    <br/>
                    <a
                        href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/cgi-bin/feedback_faq/${sessionScope.context.stateOrDefault.abbreviation}?fbtype=subentry"
                        >Contact Customer Support</a>

                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="main">

                <div class="column1">
                    <div id="nav">
                        <div>1.
                            <a href="#step1">Consider your needs</a>
                        </div>
                        <div>2.
                            <a href="#step2">Understand your options</a>
                        </div>
                        <div>3.
                            <a href="#step3">Narrow the field</a>
                        </div>
                        <div>4.
                            <a href="#step4">Dig into the details</a>
                        </div>
                        <div>5.
                            <a href="#step5">Visit and select schools</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="column2">
                    <div class="panel">

                        <h3>
             1. Consider your needs
                            <![CDATA[<a name="step1"> </a>]]>
                        </h3>
                        <p> Rank your priorities for your child and family as you begin your school
        search.
                            <br/>
      First, get a quick primer to organize your thoughts:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="308"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="307"/>
                        </ul>
                        <br/>
                        <div class="pdfs">
                            <a href="#getacro">
                                <img class="pdf" src="res/img/adobe/pdficon.gif" alt="PDF Format"/>
                            </a>

      Then, use these printable worksheets to rank your priorities
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/pdf/articles/picky/ChildQuickThink.pdf">Child Quick Think: What Strengths, Challenges and Other Characteristics
      Stand Out About Your Child?</a>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/pdf/articles/picky/FamilyQuickThink.pdf">Family Quick Think: What Values, Needs, Strengths and Challenges
      Stand Out About Your Family?</a>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/pdf/choosing_imagine.pdf">Imagining Your Ideal School: An Exercise for Setting Priorities</a>
                                </li>
                            </ul>

                        </div>
                        <h3>
2. Understand your options
                            <![CDATA[<a name="step2"> </a>]]>
                        </h3>
                        <p>
Learn what school choices you really have, and understand more about each: public,
      private, charter; district transfers; and more.</p>
                        <p>Review this first:      </p>
                        <ul>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="96"/>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Then, read more about what interests you most:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="249"/>

                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="239"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="252"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="220"/>

                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="51"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="225"/>

                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="197"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="246"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="241"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="92"/>

                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="306"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="293"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="302"/>

                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="188"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="205"/>
                        </ul>


                        <h3>
3. Narrow the field
                            <![CDATA[<a name="step3"> </a>]]>
                        </h3>

                        <p>
Use interactive search to identify an area, or to focus in on the schools that
      match your priorities for your child and family.
                        </p>

                        <h4>
                            <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/cgi-bin/site/rank_overview.cgi/${sessionScope.context.stateOrDefault.abbreviation}">Top-rated
      schools</a>
                        </h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
See which schools get four or five stars based on our exclusive ratings.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <h4>
                            <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/cgi-bin/msl_confirm/${sessionScope.context.stateOrDefault.abbreviation}">My School List
                            </a>
                        </h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
Save your potential matches for quick access to on future visits to GreatSchools.net.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <h4>
                            <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/cgi-bin/cs_where/${sessionScope.context.stateOrDefault.abbreviation}">Compare schools</a>
                        </h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
Compare schools based on criteria that matter most to you.
                            </li>
                            <li>
Line up schools side by side to compare their one- to five- star ratings
                                <c:if test="${sessionScope.context.state.yellowFlagState}">
and to see which have yellow flag alerts highlighting
areas of potential concern</c:if>.
                            </li>
                        </ul>


                        <h3>
	  4. Dig into the details
                            <![CDATA[<a name="step4"> </a>]]>
                        </h3>
                        <p>
                            <c:choose>
                                <c:when test="${sessionScope.context.state.yellowFlagState}">
                        Analyze key information about each school: exclusive ratings, real parents'
      reviews, and possible areas of concerns highlighted with yellow flag alerts.
                                </c:when>
                                <c:otherwise>
Analyze key information about each school including
      exclusive ratings and real parents' reviews.
                                </c:otherwise>
                            </c:choose>
                        </p>
                        <p>
Start with schools you've saved to
                            <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/cgi-bin/msl_confirm/${sessionScope.context.stateOrDefault.abbreviation}">My&#160;School&#160;List</a>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Or, look up school information by individual school:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/cgi-bin/ratingsrch/${sessionScope.context.stateOrDefault.abbreviation}">One-to-Five
        Star Ratings</a>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/cgi-bin/commentsrch/${sessionScope.context.stateOrDefault.abbreviation}">Parent Reviews</a>
                            </li>
                            <c:if test="${sessionScope.context.state.yellowFlagState}">
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/cgi-bin/ratingsrch/${sessionScope.context.stateOrDefault.abbreviation}">Yellow Flag Alerts</a>
                                </li>
                            </c:if>
                        </ul>

                        <h3>
		5. Visit and select schools
                            <![CDATA[<a name="step5"> </a>]]>
                        </h3>
No amount of research can replace an in-person visit to the schools you're considering.
Make sure you get the most out of each school visit by targeting what questions
to ask and what to look for.
                        <p>Start here:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="48"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="20"/>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="pdfs">
                            <a href="#getacro">
                                <img class="pdf" src="res/img/adobe/pdficon.gif" alt="PDF Format"/>
                            </a>
        Document specific questions about individual schools based on your research
        with these printable worksheets:
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/pdf/schq_visit_elem.pdf">The Elementary
        School Visit: A Step by Step Guide</a>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/pdf/schq_visit_middle.pdf">The Middle
        School Visit: A Step by Step Guide</a>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://${sessionScope.context.hostName}/pdf/schq_visit_high.pdf">The High
         School Visit: A Step by Step Guide</a>

                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
        Then read these:
                        <ul>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="249"/>
                            <gsml:articleLinkLi articleId="60"/>
                        </ul>

                        <![CDATA[<div style="height:100px;"></div>]]>
                        <hr/>
                        Our worksheets are in PDF format. Go
                        <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/readermain.html" target="_blank">here</a> to get the Adobe Acrobat Reader:
                        <br/>
                        <br/>
                        <a name="getacro"
                            style="border: 0"
                            href="http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/readermain.html" target="_blank">
                            <img src="res/img/adobe/getacro.gif" alt="Get Adobe Acrobat"/>
                        </a>

                        <![CDATA[<div style="height:200px;"></div>]]>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>

            <div id="footer">
                <jsp:include page="/footer/copyright.module"/>
            </div>

            <gsml:fireclick pageType="home" pageName="five steps"/>

        </body>
    </html>
